The '''Space Pirate Boogie''' was a traditional [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]]<ref name="Slugthrowers">{{SW|url=news/slugthrowers-part-2|series=Slugthrowers: An Overview of Popular Music and Musicians in a Galaxy Far, Far Away|text=Part 2|nolive=1}}</ref> folk dance.<ref name="Zorba">''[[Zorba the Hutt's Revenge]]''</ref> The Corellian [[Music/Legends|folk-singer]] [[Grondorn Muse]] was known for breaking out in the Space Pirate Boogie at the end of his performances prior to being blacklisted by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Slugthrowers" /> In [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' places the events of ''[[Zorba the Hutt's Revenge]]'' in [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]].</ref> the Corellian [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] hosted a housewarming party at his [[Han Solo's sky house|sky house]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]], where the hired [[Band/Legends|band]] knew all of his favorite Corellian folk dances. Solo taught his romantic partner [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] the Space Pirate Boogie at the party.<ref name="Zorba" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Space Pirate Boogie first appeared in the [[1992]] junior novel ''[[Zorba the Hutt's Revenge]]'', written by [[Paul Davids|Paul]] and [[Hollace Davids]].<ref name="Zorba" />

